<!--    INTEGRATING C FUNCTIONS INTO JAVA PROGRAMS    -->
    
<tr>
    <td>
	<!WA31><a href=http://www.cs.duke.edu/~gadde/Java/tutorial/native/index.html><!WA32><img src=http://www.cs.duke.edu/~gadde/Java/tutorial/images/nativeTrail.gif width=40 height=40 border=0></a>
    </td>
    <td>
	<!WA33><a href=http://www.cs.duke.edu/~gadde/Java/tutorial/native/index.html>Integrating Native Methods into Java Programs</a> --
	These lessons show you everything you need to know to
	write native methods in the Java language. A native method is a Java method
	whose implementation is provided in another programming language such as C.
	This lesson includes step-by-step instructions
	and a comprehensive example program.
